# migrated from tests/cases/self_preference_recent.chat (gen346, hermetic + isolated)
[mock hermetic]
!set PARROT0_BASE=
!set PARROT0_SESSION=
!set PARROT0_WORLD_FACTS=0
!set PARROT0_LANG=en
!reset

[test self_preference_recent]
# gen333 (LLMSCORE Q10): a second-person recent-interest question is about
# parrot0, not a story the user just told.  Route it to the existing honest
# self-preference knowledge; never fabricate a recent hobby or experience.
> What's something you've been into lately that you've been enjoying?
< I don't have real preferences, but for the prompt I'd pick reading quietly and listening to the rain.
> Have you been enjoying any hobbies lately?
< No genuine preferences here: I don't experience days or hobbies. What's your take?

# Deictic control: first person describes the USER and remains conversational.
> I've been into pottery lately.
< Interesting -- what got you into it?

